import React from 'react'; import './About.css'; function About(){ return(

About Me

I'm a Master's student in Business Analytics (aka Data Science for Businesses) at Rady School of Management at UC San Diego. Prior to my master's, I did my undergraduate at UC San Diego in International Studies - Economics, where I first encountered simple regression models in Econometrics class. I soon became fascinated by what we can with Data, and since then, I have been working my way out to become an effective Data Scientist. In my master's, I am learning Business-focused analytics (e.g., Customer analytics, Fraud analytics, Pricing Analytics), Data Science methodologies (e.g., Baysian learning, Working with unstructured data), and Big Data tools (e.g., SQL, Hadoop, Cloud computing.)

Besides Academia, I work as a Data Analyst for The Neurosciences Department at UC San Diego. Speficically, I work for The Study of Latinos - Investigation of Neurocognitive Aging (SOL-INCA), where I implement survey generalized models to investigate hypothesized associations between Neurocognitive aging and other health conditions. To effectively demonstrate the results of statistical analyses, I create interactive graphical user interface using Shiny.

Lastly, three things that make me an effective Data Scientist are that I am an fast learner, always willing to learn, and high achiever. As I am graduating in December 2021, I am actively seeking a full-time role as a Data Scientist. If my background aligns with the type of Data scientist you are searching for, please contact me. Please check out my projects below, LinkedIn or resume.

) }; export default About;
